<!-- CHAP 01 — PRODUCTS -->
<section class="fq-chap" id="chap-products">
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="fq-chap__head">
      <div class="fq-chap__num">CHAPTER 01</div>
      <h2 class="s-title">About <em>our products</em>.</h2>
      <p class="s-sub">What's inside, who they're for, and how they compare with what you may have tried before.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="fq-list">
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">What are the three Shiōrra products?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a"><strong>Iron+</strong> is a complete hematinic for pregnancy &amp; postpartum. <strong>Ginger+</strong> is a gentle daily support for first-trimester nausea. <strong>EnergyOne+</strong> is a caffeine-free, multi-nutrient daily energy support for busy adults. All three share the same active-form formulation philosophy.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">What makes Shiōrra Iron+ different from regular iron tablets?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Iron+ uses <strong>Ferrous Bisglycinate</strong> — a chelated form of iron that's 2-4× better absorbed and ~90% gentler than ferrous sulfate. It also includes the B12, folate, B6 and zinc co-factors most conventional tablets skip.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Is the folate in Iron+ active?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Yes. We use <strong>L-methylfolate</strong> (570 mcg) — the active form. No enzymatic conversion required, which means it works even for women with the MTHFR variant.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">What's in Ginger+?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Standardized Ginger Extract (250 mg) + active <strong>B6 as P5P</strong> (2.3 mg) + Vitamin B1 + Magnesium Bisglycinate. Built specifically for first-trimester nausea and gentle daily digestion.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Is EnergyOne+ caffeine-free?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Yes — 100% caffeine-free. It uses Taurine + Ginseng extract + B-Complex + minerals + amino acids to support your body's natural energy systems. Not a stimulant, not a crash.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Are all Shiōrra products vegetarian?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Yes. Every Shiōrra capsule is 100% vegetarian — vegecap shells, no gelatin, no animal-derived ingredients.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CHAP 02 — PREGNANCY -->
<section class="fq-chap fq-chap--alt" id="chap-pregnancy">
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="fq-chap__head">
      <div class="fq-chap__num">CHAPTER 02</div>
      <h2 class="s-title">Pregnancy &amp; <em>safety</em>.</h2>
      <p class="s-sub">Safe to combine, safe for trimesters — and when to talk to your gynaecologist.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="fq-list">
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Can I take Iron+ throughout pregnancy?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Yes — Iron+ is designed for use throughout pregnancy and postpartum. Always confirm with your OB-GYN, particularly if your current hemoglobin is on the very low end.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Can I take Iron+ and Ginger+ together?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Yes — they pair well. Many moms take Ginger+ in the morning (for nausea) and Iron+ later in the day. Both are gentle enough for daily use.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Is Ginger+ safe in the first trimester?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Yes — Ginger+ was built specifically for first-trimester nausea. The doses of ginger and B6 are pregnancy-friendly. If symptoms are severe or persistent, please consult your gynaecologist.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Is EnergyOne+ safe in pregnancy?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">EnergyOne+ contains ginseng extract, which is typically <strong>not recommended during pregnancy</strong>. For pregnant or breastfeeding women, we recommend Iron+ and/or Ginger+ instead and a chat with your doctor before adding any new supplement.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">Will Iron+ cause constipation or nausea?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">It's significantly less likely than conventional iron. Ferrous Bisglycinate is ~90% gentler on the GI tract. If you do feel queasy, take it with food, with plenty of water, and pair with Ginger+ during the first trimester.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CHAP 03 — ROUTINE -->
<section class="fq-chap" id="chap-routine">
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="fq-chap__head">
      <div class="fq-chap__num">CHAPTER 03</div>
      <h2 class="s-title">Your daily <em>routine</em>.</h2>
      <p class="s-sub">When to take, with food or not, and what to do if you miss a day.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="fq-list">
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">When should I take Iron+?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Once a day, ideally with a meal. Avoid pairing with tea, coffee or calcium-rich drinks within an hour — they can blunt iron absorption. Vitamin C-rich foods (citrus, amla) help.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">When should I take Ginger+?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Once a day, anytime. Many women take it in the morning when nausea tends to peak. You can take it with or without food.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">When should I take EnergyOne+?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Once a day, anytime. Most people take it in the morning. Caffeine-free, so it won't interfere with sleep if you take it later in the day.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">How long until I notice a difference?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Most women report the first improvements within 1-2 weeks (settling, less fatigue) and meaningful changes by week 4. With Iron+, hemoglobin usually rises steadily over 3-6 months.</div></details>
      <details class="fq-item"><summary class="fq-q">What if I miss a day?<span class="plus">+</span></summary><div class="fq-a">Just take the next dose on schedule — don't double up. Consistency matters more than perfection.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

